The paper deals with algorithms for approximating the length of the longest increasing sequence and the length of the longest common subsequence, which are both problems in the area of data structures (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The algorithms are designed to work in the data stream model, which involves limited memory usage and efficient processing of data, making it relevant to the areas of algorithms and complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of dynamic programming, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
